<li><i><a href="/wiki/Protect_and_Survive" title="Protect and Survive">Protect and Survive</a></i>, the 1970s British government information films on nuclear war.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/List_of_nuclear_holocaust_fiction" title="List of nuclear holocaust fiction">List of nuclear holocaust fiction</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Nuclear_weapons_in_popular_culture" title="Nuclear weapons in popular culture">Nuclear weapons in popular culture</a></li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_War_Game" title="The War Game">The War Game</a></i>, a 1960s BBC docudrama about the effects of nuclear war that was not broadcast until the 1980s</li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_Day_After" title="The Day After">The Day After</a></i>, an American made-for-television film which also portrays the buildup to and the after-effects of large-scale nuclear war</li>
</ul>
